title: American_Top_40_1982_October_30th
description:
"Every week we count down the 40 biggest hits in the USA from King Cove, Alaska, to King City, Missouri; from King of Prussia, Pennsylvania, to King Hill, Idaho. Up two notches to number 20, here's Evelyn King with her number one soul song, "Love Come Down."


American Top 40 with Casey Kasem aired on radio from July 4, 1970 until August 6, 1988. This is a recording of a rebroadcast from internet radio.

In this broadcast:

Debuting in the hot 100 all the way up at number 31 is Supertramp with their hit song, "It's Raining Again."

Rush is at number 21 with their first top 40 hit, "New World Man."

Two listeners want to know, "In the rock era, what color has appeared in the most number one song titles?" The winning color has seven number one titles to it's credit.

Casey lists the three women with the most top 40 hits in the post Beatles period. The top two are in this countdown and, as of this broadcast, have 21 and 23 top 40 hits respectively.
